  "text": "The Kafka consumer heartbeat session timeout mechanism is defined across multiple files:\n\n1. **Heartbeat Session Timeout Threshold Definition**:\n   - `GroupRebalanceConfig.java` (line 41) defines the `sessionTimeoutMs` field which stores the session timeout value\n   - `ConsumerConfig.java` (line 440-444) defines the configuration with a default value of 45000 milliseconds (45 seconds)\n   - The configuration is retrieved via `CommonClientConfigs.SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`\n\n2. **Session Timeout Check Implementation**:\n   - `Heartbeat.java` (lines 119-122) contains the `sessionTimeoutExpired(long now)` method which checks if the session timer has expired\n   - The Heartbeat class is initialized with the session timeout value in its constructor (line 52) via `time.timer(config.sessionTimeoutMs)`\n   - The session timer is reset when a heartbeat is successfully received via `receiveHeartbeat()` method (line 102)\n\n3. **Session Timeout Handling in Consumer Polling Loop**:\n   - `AbstractCoordinator.java` contains the `HeartbeatThread` inner class (line 1454) which runs the heartbeat loop\n   - In the `HeartbeatThread.run()` method (lines 1513-1517), the heartbeat session timeout is checked during each polling iteration\n   - When `heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now)` returns true, the method calls `markCoordinatorUnknown(\"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\")`\n   - This logs an informational message (line 1006-1008) indicating that the group coordinator is unavailable due to the session timeout\n\nThe complete flow is: Consumer polls → HeartbeatThread checks sessionTimer → If expired, calls markCoordinatorUnknown which logs the timeout and disconnects from the coordinator, forcing the consumer group to rebalance."
}

